I was visiting some family in the area (I live pretty far away), but saw that this restaurant was open and wanted to bring some food over to my aunt's. I picked up the "Creamy Shrimp Pesto Pizza" and was very happy with the results. Each piece of shrimp was larger than I expected it to be, but hey, I'm not complaining! When I come back to the area again, I will definitely stop by! Also, the outside had a lot of areas to take cute pictures. I have a feeling this restaurant will be the next trendy "go-to" spot for many, so I'm glad I found this place before it starts blowing up! I'm excited to see the growth and changes to come once dining is allowed again.</Text>

<Review>I usually don't review or give my opinion, but I was compelled to say something about this place!
It's like having an upscale Beverly Hills restaurant right here in Burbank.
The attention to detail in every dish, my god, the pizza crust, the salads...
can't say enough. I think one reason is they have a very specific menu, it's not pages long so they can focus on gourmet dishes and not a bunch of secondary dishes.
Look, it's not on a hill overlooking the city, it's on Glenoaks, but the interior is upscale and there's a window looking into the kitchen in the waiting area, how many restaurants have that much confidence in their chef. Save your time and money going to Beverly Hills, eat here!<//Review><pics>None<//pics>< response>

< review>
My boyfriend and I decided to order take-out as a good friend of ours was raving about this place and especially the pizzas. We drove all the way from West LA to Burbank last weekend since there's not as much traffic lately. I'm a Margherita kind of pizza girl so we ordered a Margherita Pizza and the Roasted Grape & Kale Salad. Both were delicious! The pizza crust was perfect and I could tell they use fresh, quality ingredients. The salad was super tasty and the flavors were well-balanced. I highly recommend this place and what we ordered. I wish we had a place like this nearby. The prices are reasonable and the staff was friendly. Good parking and they have a cute patio area for outdoor seating. I also felt good about supporting a newly opened small business. Definitely check this place out!<//review>

< Review>

1. BRUSCHETTA (Appetizer) ðŸ’›
10/10, I would recommend this to EVERYONE. My brother ordered this and I took a bite to try and almost finished the entire plate myself! I donâ€™t even like tomatoes, yet I found this to be my favorite appetizer. Fresh, healthy, and packs a flavorful punch. Definitely coming back for more.

2. Meat & Potatoes (Appetizer) ðŸ’›
The appetizer is one of the larger portion sizes, so it should be shared amongst a few people, or it can be eaten as a meal for one. These meatballs are very hearty. The potatoes are whipped to perfection and the entire dish comes together with the gravy dressing. The dressing consists of this earthy, mushroom flavor and it is not too heavy so it goes well with the meat and potatoes. I had some gravy leftover and used it to dip with my fries! Delicious, delicious, delicious.

3. Sweet Sopressata (Pizza) ðŸ’›
Wowâ€¦ I have eaten a lot of pizza in my lifetime, and I havenâ€™t tried anything like the Sweet Sopressata before. The sweetness comes from the honey and I never thought of a pizza combination with that ingredient. This dish was very impressive, to say the least.

4. Insalate (Pizza) ðŸ’›
This pizza has definitely become a staple for my family. The sweetness from the fig compliments the prosciutto very well. The pizza is topped with arugula and herb ricotta cheese. There are a lot of components to this pizza and it comes with a nice presentation for that Instagram post!<//Review>

< Review>
My wife and I arrived here around 2:30 pm for a late lunch and ordered through the drive-thru window. We placed our orders and found a nice shaded area under a tree to park and enjoy our meals. My wife and I both ordered the number to combos which consisted of the Texas Double Whopper medium drink and fries. I ordered onion rings in place of the fries. I also requested the zesty onion ring sauce as well as assorted sauces and ketchup for my meals. After sorting out our food, I looked in our bags and couldn't find any sauces or ketchup. This slightly annoyed me to say the least. My wife said, don't worry about it I'll go back inside and get them. When she came back, we began to start our eating. When I wrapped my Whopper, I noticed that it was a single Patty and and it was missing the extras. My wife checked hers and it was the exact same. At this point, I was very upset. We looked at our receipt, and apparently they took down our order incorrectly. This infuriated me. At this point, I wouldn't side and spoke to the manager and told him what had happened. He explained that we ordered the wrong meals and would happily fix it, but we will be charged for the extra patties. I told him that they incorrectly processed our orders and I wanted them to correct it and no extra charge because this was the second time in less than 10 minutes that they messed up our orders. He agreed, corrected are workers and we went on our way. We finished our meals and went home shortly thereafter. We probably won't be visiting this Burger King again. Not recommended.</Review>

We came in at 5:30, they closed at 6 and were still able to take us and we were seated right away.

On Thursday my index finger nails started to lift and by Sunday they were off. I was upset because I work in an office and only type, so for the nails to come completely off in less than a week is awful! I tried calling the salon and when I finally got through, I explained my situation to Billy (who has excellent customer service!) he told me to come in and heâ€™d have it taken care of. I came in, was seated with Nikki within 5 minutes of my arrival time and was done within 7.  I was handed a ticket to pay and when I got back to Billy, he took care of it for me.

Overall I would go back, (Pros)
- they do styles well and have an abundance of supplies to do many different styles/designs.
- they are quick
- Billy is great
- I received a lot of compliments on my nails
- when I got the replacement nails, the nail tech knew what she needed and exactly how to do them without asking!

Cons
- my nails broke in less than a week
- it was $70 for just the full set. (Thatâ€™s a little high, especially if you have to get your nails done weekly because they lift)
- they never told me the price up front (which I think should always be told because each place charges differently)
- a third nail just lifted and Nikkiâ€™s nails arenâ€™t quite matching the other ones, now that itâ€™s had time to settle.

But I will definitely give them another shot. Itâ€™s rare you find good customer service at these kinds of establishments.

For those who wonâ€™t try them again:
Pink and White Nails in union city are great!
Lavender is second, and Nu Nails (Southland Mall area near Chase) is really great.
All less expensive and do really good jobs.

Update: since I posted this review on Monday 7/15/19, I lost another nail and 3 have lifted! Would not recommend this salon unless you just want your nails on for a couple days.<//Text>

< Review>
Our home in Upland was built in 2011. The builder used builder's grade, double pane windows. We live near a busy road so traffic has been a problem because our windows are very large and let a lot of sound in.

We decided to replace all of our upstairs windows with Infinity by Marvin after seeing them at a Home Show in Ontario. These new windows are very well made. They slide open and closed very easily; much easier than our other windows. I clean my windows monthly and was very happy to see how easy they tilt inwards.

The new windows helped reduce the sound coming into our bedrooms at night. They didn't reduce the sound entirely, but definitely helped. The installers also helped by insulating the area around the windows, sealing them tight. The installers did a good job with their finishing work.

One of the signs of a good company is owner interaction. After the job was done, the owner followed up to ensure we were happy with our purchase and the job done by his installers.

We are pleased with our purchase.< /Review>

<Text>Like most homes, to get to our backyard we had to go through a sliding glass door.  This was not an easy task for my husband who is in a wheelchair.  First, someone had to put a ramp in front of the door, then mats across the rails of the slider, and then another ramp to the outside.  We thought by taking out the slider and putting French doors in would solve this problem.  However we still had thresholds that were difficult to cross and now a door that was too narrow, and yes, we still had the ramps.   When I met your sales rep at the Home Show, I told him our dilemma and he said he could design a special door.  He came to the house and took measurements, and designed a beautiful French door that was extra wide to allow for the width of a wheelchair.  Furthermore he suggested a special threshold that was ADA compliant.  The installers who came to the house were efficient and courteous.  They cleaned up thoroughly when they were finished.  They took away my old door and wooden ramps and left me with a beautiful French door that matched my front door perfectly.  There is now no need for ugly ramps or mats, for my husband can now go outside through our new door without any problems with tracks, uneven thresholds or too narrow of a door.  All of which I was told by other window companies could not be done.  This is a long review, but people with disabilities need to know there is a company that can accommodate your special needs. < Review>
Sushi Confidential has two locations in the South Bay: San Jose and Campbell, both located in California. The location I will review and went to today was at the Downtown Campbell location. The downtown Campbell is located in Campbell, CA where there are a bunch of restaurants and little family owned stores. Right now, Sushi Confidential is doing take-out orders and outdoor dining due to COVID-19 and I saw the staff and the customers handling the protocols pretty good. I got my order pretty quickly and when I got home and ate the sushi, it was so delicious! I ordered 4 of their vegetarian rolls since I am a flexitarian.

The first roll I will review is their Anti- Phishing which is with spicy tofu, tempered green beans, topped with ahimi, avocado, unagi sauce, green onions. Ahimi is basically a play on raw tuna but itâ€™s not raw tuna, itâ€™s tomato but has that ahi tuna feel. To be fair, I thought there was no way tofu can be put into a sushi roll but it turns out they did! I really liked the tofu with the unagi sauce and avocado, I thought it gave the roll a nice freshness. I also liked how the tofu was soft and it actually had flavor that I absolutely enjoyed! I also liked the ahimi which was soft and it did taste like it was raw tuna but itâ€™s not! I enjoyed how I can still have that â€œtunaâ€ taste without eating any fish. I did wish the tofu was a bit spicier. I was expecting it to be slightly more spicy. To be fair, this was actually my favorite roll out of the 4 I got! Highly recommend this roll very much!

The second roll I got was their Snitch which is spicy tofu, cucumber, topped with avocado, spicy spy sauce, and sweet potato crisps. This roll was definitely spicer than the first roll which I really liked I thought that this roll had spicer tofu than the Anti-Phishing which I liked very much! I liked the avocado and cucumber so that the roll had some freshness and I like the spicy spy sauce, it complemented the roll very well. I did like the addition of the sweet potato crips, really nice texture element I do wish it was a bit crunchier. Overall, really liked the roll, it had every tasting element you should definitely taste ina sushi roll.

The third roll I got was DTF (Down to Fiesta) which is basically an avocado roll topped with fresh pico de gallo, jalapenos, Persian lime & jalapeno olive oil, sesame seeds. This was a really nice, fresh roll and l liked the addition of the other ingredients to help elevate the flavors of the sushi roll. I think a bit of lemon maybe would of helped get another flavor level of the sushi roll because I didnâ€™t taste acidity which I think thatâ€™s what pico de gallo really needs. Either a lemon or lime would of helped the roll out more and tie in the flavors together. I do however really liked the fun fresh flavors they were going for I thought it was thought out!

The last roll I got was their Hollaback which has shiitake mushroom, cucumber, topped with avocado, lemon, garlic crisp, soy vinaigrette, and spicy sprouts. I really liked how mild this sushi roll was and all of the vegetables really helped tie the sushi roll together. I did like the lemon on top to give the roll acidity. I thought that was smart so all of the flavor components shined through. I did like the addition to the shiitake mushrooms because those were like the â€œmeatâ€ part of the sushi roll which was super filling. Overall, this sushi roll was delicious and perfect. I donâ€™t have anything to say except, this was some great fresh sushi!

Overall, I really liked Sushi Confidential and this is definitely a must go spot if your ever in Campbell or San Jose! Their sushi rolls were very fresh and the rice was just right! Donâ€™t forget to support local businesses like this one and check out their sushi! Itâ€™s really delicious and I love the variety of vegetarian/vegan sushi rolls! I wish there was more because I have a feeling their rolls are terrific and definitely I hope they come out with more vegetarian options in the future! Follow me @the.flexitarian.aholic on Instagram for more Bay Area eats!< /Review>

<Name>Lorral Whaley< /Name>< time>
1600648957035< /time>
<rate>5< /rate>< Review>
Went today on a Sunday. Looked like it started to pick up after the 49er game was over but everyone kept their distance. They had a great set up. We gave them our name and it was about a 15 minute wait so we walked around until the table was ready. They have little signs stating I'd the table was clean or dirty. Also, they had a sign for you to scan the menu from your phone. When you were ready to order you went to the table at the entrance. They have plexiglass separating you from the cashier. They even sanitized your card before swiping. They do add an 18% gratuity to your order for the whole staff to split, which is a great idea! They bring you ice water in plastic cups and a vase with ice cold water for you to refill yourself. Everyone had masks. Food was great! Sad they didn't have the green bean tower anymore but got the edamame instead. Those were addicting! Had a side of miso soup. We also ordered the spicy salmon roll (brought tears to my bf's eyes ðŸ¤£) and I had the geisha roll. The avocado with tempura were delicious. The sriracha mayo sauce with it was spicy but a good spicy. My brother in law got the bento box (which was huge!) The portions were great. My sister in law ordered from the vegan menu and was not disappointed. She had these cute crunchy sweet potatoes curled on her tofu roll. Super yummy! Great service and great tasting food. It was the perfect day to visit downtown Campbell. Not cheap but definitely tasty and worth the extra few bucks. Can't wait to come back here!<//Review>

< Text>
The sushi is good, nothing too crazy but pretty good. Some roles we had were better than others. What I really appreciated about this place was all the cleaning measures they took due to covid. Not only they clean every table after each customer they even clean the chairs. They don't take reservations but they have a pretty good system for putting your name on the list. They have a QR code for menu. One draw back is you have to order at the door, but it's in a way safer and I don't mind it. They staff ask you to put your mask on when they bring your food, sure can be slightly annoying specially if you're already drinking or eating but I appreciate them being so a safe and protecting their staff & customers.
Definitely a place I trust through covid.< /Text>

< text>
I have no complaints about this sushi restaurant, fully admitting I am not the kind of person who asks whether they have fresh uni today, or whatever it is serious sushi people ask.You can get a roll with crunchy things and spicy mayo sauce, totally satisfying those of us with less rarified palates.

I gave it higher stars for two main reasons:
1) It is delightful to sit on the patio here for lunch during a Sunday farmer's market, and
2) The kids' meal is in my top 5 kids meals I have encountered. It has real fruit AND real vegetables in it. The day we were there I joyfully watched my toddler eat edamame and fresh strawberries instead of just tan things from the deep frier. It comes with very yummy sweet potato fries, which I ate most of for my kid. There are many options, including salmon. A delight.<//text>

1</rating>
<GmapID>0x808e34df1138295d:0xef39b8d601349874<//GmapID><text>I'm not sure how this place ever became so popular, but I suppose everyone has their own priorities.

The top of my sushi scale is currently Izaka-ya, which is like someone ripped a restaurant up out of Japanese soil by its roots and slammed it back down by the San Jose airport.
Sushi Confidential is seated solidly at the bottom, just above the sushi they serve at Google X (which is invariably soggy and tastes the way mildew smells). It's pretty uncommon for me to be able to pinpoint a restaurant's exact location in my internal rating scale, but this one is easy.

When we tried eating here, we had a very difficult time with their menu, which is heavily westernized. As I recall, nearly every sushi roll was spicy or contained nuts or another oddball element.
I don't recall what I wound up ordering - one of the traditional rolls, maybe a rainbow - but I do remember remarking that their creativity must be for the sake of hiding the flavour of the fish, itself. My wife was similarly unhappy with her food, but the real showstopper was the tempura shrimp and vegetables which, within a single dish, exhibited a range from overcooked mush to still having ice on it. This seemed to confirm my suspicion that the fish was from frozen.
Overall, it was a very poor showing. I could argue that we only caught them on a bad day, but it's pretty tough to recover from serving food from frozen, particularly when you are a sushi restaurant. Fresh fish is sort of the entire idea.

The service was good.
When the waitress served us, she accidentally dropped some of the food on the table and then left it there, which we found surprising and tactless. Later on in the meal, a waiter overheard us discussing the low-quality food and odd service and immediately reported it to a manager, who came over to personally apologize and ask for feedback. We thought her attentiveness and the fact that a server cared enough to escalate what he'd overheard spoke well of their staff. The tempura was removed from our bill.

Not interested in trying again.<//text><response>None< /response>< user_name>
Rebecca Hassinger< /user_name>
</record>
</dataset><record>

Please STAY away from the Tuna POKE BOWL unless you want to feel like Cosbyâ€™s last victim, drugged, disoriented, confused and battered.

I would recommend to just drink the yellow murky tap water that the city of Campbell has to offer. It was hard not to notice the noise coming from the kitchen, loud music from the speaker, loud game on TV and people yelling at each other. I also love when elderly people just let themselves go and drink and act like Vikings disregarding their surroundings, very entertaining to watch, but not fun when it is happening five feet away from you, what a pretty mess and eyesore at the same time. If you just had a hip or knee replacement and just want to party like a rock star this place will fit you perfectly.

<Review>F*****g right five stars. Don't confuse the 'bro' like ambience for an upscale rubios tacos. This place has extremely fresh and delicious sushi (no rainbow or sushi rolls on fire reviews here). The staff is a hybrid of hipsters and sushi geeks that give the usual sushi chef line up a run for their money. They're really creative too.

If you're looking for the Asian ambience of your run of the mill sushi spot, you're better off at pf  changs.

However if you want truly fresh and authentic sushi in Campbell, this is your spot.< /Review>< gmap_id>

<name>Kimberly Ann Graham< /name><Time>1494711969303<//Time>< rate>
4<//rate>
<Text>One of my favorite sushi places.  Period!

The happy hour is really good.  3 to 6 and 10 to close EVERY DAY!  Great prices on a good selection of rolls including some of their specialty rolls.  The tempura avocado is on there as a starter and I could just eat the entire plate of melt in your mouth deliciousness!  So good!

I also love the Cabo Conspiracy and the California Confidential.  The edamame trio is pretty darn good.  3 different sauces and enough for 6, a bit much for 2 to share.  Take the leftovers of it home.

One of the best things is the outdoor seating on the sidewalk.  Downtown Campbell is a lovely place to be on a warm spring/summer/fall day and to sit outside and people watch while enjoying some great sushi is a beautiful thing!

Edit 5/2017 handicap accessible bar!!  ðŸ˜

Yeah, I'll be going again and again!  #ReviewLocal< /Text>< pics>

<pics>None</pics><Text>I'm extremely dissapointed in the quality of the food we got last night.
We've been going to Sushi Confidential for a few years now. and they've usually provided pretty good sushi.  Working 2 jobs and having a new untrained puppy, I've been ordering via Door Dash a lot lately. And again, usually the quality is good and the food comes very quickly.
We decided to order in from Sushi Confidential last night after a long day of travel.

We ordered A LOT. Ramen for my non sushi loving dog sitter, 5 rolls and salmon nigiri for the rest of us.
So when the food was running late, and our Door Dasher had to text to say he was still waiting, we weren't upset.  The food was delivered about a half hour late, again, we weren't upset. Until we divided up and we all dug in. My dog sitter loved her ramen, so that was nice.
But the sushi rolls were horrible.  Some were rolled in half cooked rice while the rest were rolled in mushy way overcooked rice. If my food is going to be late, I expect it to be properly cooked.  We also received sashimi and not nigiri. Which I mean.. we could have let that slide. But nothing was good about the rolls we received.  And I spent well over $100 on a garbage meal.  I've already alerted DoorDash, but this isn't their fault, our Dasher was great. It was the restaurant who failed us last night.

1427173874008<//Time>
<rating>4</rating>< Text>
The food is ok, the service is ok.

We came here for dinner one night, ordered the garlic edamame $6, and it was pretty tasty. We also ordered the Geisha girl roll $15 which was ok, a bit too much rice on it and really expensive for a roll. The tonkasu ramen $15 was a huge bowl of salty goodness, the broth was flavorful and there was a lot of pork in it. The only problem was the ramen was a giant clum and not cooked throughly. I spoke to the waiter about it and he immediately took it back and made me a new one.

The manager came over and apologized for it and offered us another dish. So we ordered the Agedashi tofu appetizer and it was a major fail. The tofu was way too sweet and kinda hard, and the tofu was deep fried in tempura batter which is completely wrong way of cooking it. In addition, the garnish was at the bottom buried under the tofu when it should be on top.

Service was attentive and we really like the outside patio seating area.</Text>
